ISLAMABAD, Dec 27 (APP):At least four passengers died when a passenger van en route to Karachi from Jamshoro met with an accident with a car on the Indus Highway on Wednesday.
According to rescue sources, four individuals died on the spot while more than fifteen others including women and children were injured after a horrified collision between a car and passenger van, a private news channel reported. The injured and bodies were shifted to the hospital by rescue teams.
